                        <interp inst="t18221204-12-victim135" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221204-12-off60 t18221204-12-victim135"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-12-person136">
                  GEORGE 
                  FINDLAY
               <interp inst="t18221204-12-person136" type="surname" value="FINDLAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-12-person136" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-12-person136" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18221204-12-viclabel62" type="occupation">seaman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221204-12-victim135 t18221204-12-viclabel62"></join>. On the 3d of November, I met the prisoner about eleven o'clock at night. I went to a house with her, but do not know where - we went to bed. I awoke at four o'clock in the morning, she was gone, and my watch and appendages. I had left it in my pocket - I slept in my clothes. My brother and cousin were with me, and came to the door to awake me. I found a pocket and some duplicates in the room, by which means I found her in bed, alone. I said I would give her two sovereigns to produce my watch - she said she knew nothing about it. My brother found it in the bed without the cases. She was quite intoxicated. I said if she would say where the cases were I would give her a sovereign - she would not and I called the officer.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-12-person137">
                  THOMAS 
                  HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18221204-12-person137" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-12-person137" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-12-person137" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. The prosecutor gave me the watch. She claimed the duplicates found in the room. I delivered them to her I believe, by order of the Magistrate.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I met him with two young men and another woman, and went with them. He only had enough to pay for the room, and gave me his watch instead of money. I gave him my direction, Brown Bear-alley.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-12-person138">
                  GEORGE 
                  FINDLAY
               <interp inst="t18221204-12-person138" type="surname" value="FINDLAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-12-person138" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-12-person138" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I only had 5 s. I gave her no money, and had not agreed to give her anything. I gave half-a-crown for the bed, and found half-a-crown in my pocket in the morning. I was rather in liquor. I did not give it her to pledge. I am sure I did not entrust her with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18221204-12-verdict63" type="verdictDescription">
